                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6700: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-07T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3546. For the Secretary of State from <persName corresp="#p_PFL"
                    >Polk</persName>.</p>
                <p>A communication from French Embassy, Washington, presented to Conference
                    yesterday stated that United States could not assist in repatriation of Czechs
                    owing to lack of shipping and suggested that they go out in the direction of
                        <persName corresp="#p_DGAI">General Denikine</persName>’s forces. Allied
                    military authorities say suggestion out of the question. Would it not be
                    possible to do something, as I understand we are to be reimbursed for any
                    expense and it would seem that we were under an obligation to do everything in
                    our power.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
